The Kwara State University (KWASU) says it will commence operations in two campuses of the institution next academic session. KWASU confirmed that the campuses are located at Osi and Ilesha-Baruba. This is contained in a statement issued by the Director, University Relations, Mr Abdulrazaq Sanni, on Monday in Ilorin. He said that it was part of the governmentâ€™s plans to meet up with the law that made KWASU a three-campus institution and to equally take care of the increasing population of students on yearly basis.